    <lmp:Comment type="FUNCTION">Insulin decreases blood glucose concentration. It increases cell permeability to monosaccharides, amino acids and fatty acids. It accelerates glycolysis, the pentose phosphate cycle, and glycogen synthesis in liver</lmp:Comment>
    <lmp:Comment type="SUBUNIT">Heterodimer of a B chain and an A chain linked by two disulfide bonds (PubMed:25423173)</lmp:Comment>
    <lmp:Comment type="TISSUE SPECIFICITY">Expressed by pancreatic beta-cells (at protein level)</lmp:Comment>
    <lmp:Comment type="PHARMACEUTICAL">Available under the names Humulin or Humalog (Eli Lilly) and Novolin (Novo Nordisk). Used in the treatment of diabetes. Humalog is an insulin analog with 52-Lys-Pro-53 instead of 52-Pro-Lys-53</lmp:Comment>
    <lmp:Comment type="SIMILARITY">Belongs to the insulin family</lmp:Comment>
